00132 static INLINE unsigned nedtriebitscanr(size_t value)
00133 {
00134 #ifdef _MSC_VER
00135   unsigned long bitpos;
00136 #if defined(_M_IA64) || defined(_M_X64) || defined(WIN64)
00137   assert(8==sizeof(size_t));
00138   _BitScanReverse64(&bitpos, value);
00139 #else
00140   assert(4==sizeof(size_t));
00141   _BitScanReverse(&bitpos, value);
00142 #endif
00143   return (unsigned) bitpos;
00144 #elif defined(__GNUC__)
00145   return sizeof(value)*__CHAR_BIT__ - 1 - (unsigned) __builtin_clz(value);
00146 #else
00147   /* The following code is illegal C, but it almost certainly will work.
00148   If not use the legal implementation below */
00149   unsigned bitpos;
00150 #if 1
00151         union {
00152                 unsigned asInt[2];
00153                 double asDouble;
00154         };
00155         int n;
00156 
00157         asDouble = (double)value + 0.5;
00158         n = (asInt[0 /*Use 1 if your CPU is big endian!*/] >> 20) - 1023;
00159 #warning Make sure you change the line above me if your CPU is big endian!
00160         return (unsigned) n;
00161 #else
00162   size_t x=value;
00163         x = x | (x >> 1);
00164         x = x | (x >> 2);
00165         x = x | (x >> 4);
00166         x = x | (x >> 8);
00167         x = x | (x >>16);
00168         x = ~x;
00169         x = x - ((x >> 1) & 0x55555555);
00170         x = (x & 0x33333333) + ((x >> 2) & 0x33333333);
00171         x = (x + (x >> 4)) & 0x0F0F0F0F;
00172         x = x + (x << 8);
00173         x = x + (x << 16);
00174         return x >> 24;
00175 #endif
00176 #endif
00177 }

00283   template<class trietype, class type, size_t fieldoffset, size_t (*keyfunct)(const type *RESTRICT)> DEBUGINLINE void trieinsert(trietype *RESTRICT head, type *RESTRICT r)
00284   {
00285     type *RESTRICT node, *RESTRICT childnode;
00286     TrieLink_t<type> *RESTRICT nodelink, *RESTRICT rlink;
00287     size_t rkey=keyfunct(r), keybit, nodekey;
00288     unsigned bitidx;
00289     int keybitset;
00290 
00291     rlink=(TrieLink_t<type> *RESTRICT)((size_t) r + fieldoffset);
00292     memset(rlink, 0, sizeof(TrieLink_t<type>));
00293     bitidx=nedtriebitscanr(rkey);
00294     assert(bitidx<NEDTRIE_INDEXBINS);
00295     if(!(node=head->triebins[bitidx]))
00296     { /* Bottom two bits set indicates a node hanging off of head */
00297       rlink->trie_parent=(type *RESTRICT)(size_t)(3|(bitidx<<2));
00298       head->triebins[bitidx]=r;
00299       goto end;
00300     }
00301     /* Avoid variable bit shifts where possible, their performance can suck */
00302     keybit=(size_t) 1<<bitidx;
00303     for(;;node=childnode)
00304     {
00305       nodelink=(TrieLink_t<type> *RESTRICT)((size_t) node + fieldoffset);
00306       nodekey=keyfunct(node);
00307       if(nodekey==rkey)
00308       { /* Insert into ring list */
00309         rlink->trie_parent=0;
00310         rlink->trie_prev=node;
00311         rlink->trie_next=nodelink->trie_next;
00312         nodelink->trie_next=r;
00313         if(rlink->trie_next) ((TrieLink_t<type> *RESTRICT)((size_t) rlink->trie_next + fieldoffset))->trie_prev=r;
00314         break;
00315       }
00316       keybit>>=1;
00317       keybitset=!!(rkey&keybit); 
00318       childnode=nodelink->trie_child[keybitset];
00319       if(!childnode)
00320       { /* Insert here */
00321         rlink->trie_parent=node;
00322         nodelink->trie_child[keybitset]=r;
00323         break;
00324       }
00325     }
00326 end:
00327     head->count++;
00328 #if NEDTRIEDEBUG
00329     triecheckvalidity<trietype, type, fieldoffset, keyfunct>(head);
00330 #endif
00331   }
00332 }

00389   template<class trietype, class type, size_t fieldoffset, size_t (*keyfunct)(const type *RESTRICT), int (*nobblefunct)(trietype *head)> DEBUGINLINE void trieremove(trietype *RESTRICT head, type *RESTRICT r)
00390   {
00391     type *RESTRICT node, **myaddrinparent=0;
00392     TrieLink_t<type> *RESTRICT nodelink, *RESTRICT childlink, *RESTRICT rlink;
00393     unsigned bitidx;
00394 
00395     rlink=(TrieLink_t<type> *RESTRICT)((size_t) r + fieldoffset);
00396     /* Am I a leaf off the tree? */
00397     if(rlink->trie_prev)
00398     { /* Remove from linked list */
00399       assert(!rlink->trie_parent);
00400       node=rlink->trie_prev;
00401       nodelink=(TrieLink_t<type> *RESTRICT)((size_t) node + fieldoffset);
00402       nodelink->trie_next=rlink->trie_next;
00403       if(rlink->trie_next)
00404       {
00405         nodelink=(TrieLink_t<type> *RESTRICT)((size_t) rlink->trie_next + fieldoffset);
00406         nodelink->trie_prev=node;
00407       }
00408       goto functexit;
00409     }
00410     /* I must therefore be part of the tree */
00411     assert(rlink->trie_parent);
00412     assert(!rlink->trie_prev);
00413     /* Am I at the top of the tree? */
00414     if(((size_t) rlink->trie_parent & 3)==3)
00415     { /* Extract my bitidx */
00416       bitidx=(unsigned)(((size_t) rlink->trie_parent)>>2);
00417       assert(head->triebins[bitidx]==r);
00418       /* Set the node addr to be modified */
00419       myaddrinparent=&head->triebins[bitidx];
00420     }
00421     else
00422     { /* Otherwise I am one of my parent's children */
00423       node=rlink->trie_parent;
00424       nodelink=(TrieLink_t<type> *RESTRICT)((size_t) node + fieldoffset);
00425       myaddrinparent=(nodelink->trie_child[0]==r) ? &nodelink->trie_child[0] : &nodelink->trie_child[1];
00426     }
00427     assert(*myaddrinparent==r);
00428     node=0;
00429     /* Can I replace me with a sibling? */
00430     if(rlink->trie_next)
00431     {
00432       node=rlink->trie_next;
00433       nodelink=(TrieLink_t<type> *RESTRICT)((size_t) node + fieldoffset);
00434       assert(nodelink->trie_prev==r);
00435       nodelink->trie_prev=0;
00436       goto end;
00437     }
00438     /* Can I simply remove myself from my parent? */
00439     if(!rlink->trie_child[0] && !rlink->trie_child[1])
00440       goto end;
00441     /* I need someone to replace me in the trie, so simply find any
00442        grandchild of mine (who has the right bits to be here) which has no children.
00443     */
00444     {
00445       type *RESTRICT *RESTRICT childaddrinparent=myaddrinparent, *RESTRICT *RESTRICT newchildaddrinparent;
00446       int nobbledir=nobblefunct(head);
00447       while(*(newchildaddrinparent=&(((TrieLink_t<type> *RESTRICT)((size_t) *childaddrinparent + fieldoffset))->trie_child[nobbledir]))
00448          || *(newchildaddrinparent=&(((TrieLink_t<type> *RESTRICT)((size_t) *childaddrinparent + fieldoffset))->trie_child[!nobbledir])))
00449         childaddrinparent=newchildaddrinparent;
00450       node=*childaddrinparent;
00451       *childaddrinparent=0;
00452     }
00453   end:
00454     if(node)
00455     {
00456       nodelink=(TrieLink_t<type> *RESTRICT)((size_t) node + fieldoffset);
00457       assert(!nodelink->trie_child[0] && !nodelink->trie_child[1]);
00458       nodelink->trie_parent=rlink->trie_parent;
00459       nodelink->trie_child[0]=rlink->trie_child[0];
00460       nodelink->trie_child[1]=rlink->trie_child[1];
00461       if(nodelink->trie_child[0])
00462       {
00463         childlink=(TrieLink_t<type> *RESTRICT)((size_t) nodelink->trie_child[0] + fieldoffset);
00464         childlink->trie_parent=node;
00465       }
00466       if(nodelink->trie_child[1])

00468         childlink=(TrieLink_t<type> *RESTRICT)((size_t) nodelink->trie_child[1] + fieldoffset);
00469         childlink->trie_parent=node;

00471     }
00472     *myaddrinparent=node;

00872   {

00875     unsigned bitidx;
00876 
00877     rlink=(TrieLink_t<type> *RESTRICT)((size_t) r + fieldoffset);
00878     /* Am I a leaf off the tree? */
00879     if(rlink->trie_prev)
00880     {
00881       assert(!rlink->trie_parent);
00882       return rlink->trie_prev;
00883     }
00884     /* Trace up my parents to prev branch */
00885     while(((size_t) rlink->trie_parent & 3)!=3)
00886     {
00887       node=rlink->trie_parent;
00888       nodelink=(const TrieLink_t<type> *RESTRICT)((size_t) node + fieldoffset);
00889       /* If I was on child[1] and there is a child[0], go to bottom of child[0] */
00890       if(nodelink->trie_child[1]==r && nodelink->trie_child[0])
00891       {
00892         node=nodelink->trie_child[0];

00899     bitidx=(unsigned)(((size_t) rlink->trie_parent)>>2);
00900     assert(head->triebins[bitidx]==r);
00901     for(bitidx--; bitidx<NEDTRIE_INDEXBINS && !(node=head->triebins[bitidx]); bitidx--);
00902     if(bitidx>=NEDTRIE_INDEXBINS) return 0;
00903   returnbottomofchild:
00904     nodelink=(const TrieLink_t<type> *RESTRICT)((size_t) node + fieldoffset);
00905     /* Follow child[1] preferentially downwards */
00906     while((child=nodelink->trie_child[1] ? nodelink->trie_child[1] : nodelink->trie_child[0]))
00907     {
00908       node=child;
00909       nodelink=(const TrieLink_t<type> *RESTRICT)((size_t) node + fieldoffset);
00910     }
00911   returnendleaf:

01159   template<class trietype, class type, size_t fieldoffset, size_t (*keyfunct)(const type *RESTRICT)> DEBUGINLINE
01160            void triecheckvaliditybranch(trietype *head, type *RESTRICT node, unsigned bitidx, TrieValidityState &state)
01161   {
01162     type *RESTRICT child;
01163     TrieLink_t<type> *RESTRICT nodelink, *RESTRICT childlink;
01164     size_t nodekey=keyfunct(node);
01165 
01166     if(nodekey<state.smallestkey) state.smallestkey=nodekey;
01167     if(nodekey>state.largestkey) state.largestkey=nodekey;
01168     nodelink=(TrieLink_t<type> *RESTRICT)((size_t) node + fieldoffset);
01169     assert(nodelink->trie_parent);
01170     child=nodelink->trie_parent;
01171     childlink=(TrieLink_t<type> *RESTRICT)((size_t) child + fieldoffset);
01172     assert(childlink->trie_child[0]==node || childlink->trie_child[1]==node);
01173     assert(node==childlink->trie_child[!!(nodekey & ((size_t) 1<<bitidx))]);
01174     assert(!nodelink->trie_prev);
01175     while((child=nodelink->trie_next))
01176     {
01177       state.leafs++;
01178       childlink=(TrieLink_t<type> *RESTRICT)((size_t) child + fieldoffset);
01179       assert(!childlink->trie_parent);
01180       assert(!childlink->trie_child[0]);
01181       assert(!childlink->trie_child[1]);
01182       assert(childlink->trie_prev);
01183       assert(!childlink->trie_next || child==((TrieLink_t<type> *RESTRICT)((size_t) childlink->trie_next + fieldoffset))->trie_prev);
01184       nodelink=childlink;
01185       state.count++;
01186     }
01187     nodelink=(TrieLink_t<type> *RESTRICT)((size_t) node + fieldoffset);
01188     state.count++;
01189     if(nodelink->trie_child[0])
01190     {
01191       state.lefts++;
01192       triecheckvaliditybranch<trietype, type, fieldoffset, keyfunct>(head, nodelink->trie_child[0], bitidx-1, state);
01193     }
01194     if(nodelink->trie_child[1])
01195     {
01196       state.rights++;
01197       triecheckvaliditybranch<trietype, type, fieldoffset, keyfunct>(head, nodelink->trie_child[1], bitidx-1, state);
01198     }

01201   template<class trietype, class type, size_t fieldoffset, size_t (*keyfunct)(const type *RESTRICT)> DEBUGINLINE void triecheckvalidity(trietype *head)
01202   {
01203 #ifndef NDEBUG
01204     type *RESTRICT node, *RESTRICT child;
01205     TrieLink_t<type> *RESTRICT nodelink, *RESTRICT childlink;
01206     unsigned n, bitidx;
01207     TrieValidityState state={0};
01208     for(n=0; n<NEDTRIE_INDEXBINS; n++)
01209     {
01210       if((node=head->triebins[n]))
01211       {
01212         size_t nodekey=keyfunct(node);
01213         state.tops++;
01214         nodelink=(TrieLink_t<type> *RESTRICT)((size_t) node + fieldoffset);
01215         bitidx=(unsigned)(((size_t) nodelink->trie_parent)>>2);
01216         assert(bitidx==n);
01217         assert(head->triebins[bitidx]==node);
01218         assert(((((size_t)-1)<<bitidx) & nodekey)==((size_t) 1<<bitidx));
01219         assert(!nodelink->trie_prev);
01220         while((child=nodelink->trie_next))
01221         {
01222           state.leafs++;
01223           childlink=(TrieLink_t<type> *RESTRICT)((size_t) child + fieldoffset);
01224           assert(!childlink->trie_parent);
01225           assert(!childlink->trie_child[0]);
01226           assert(!childlink->trie_child[1]);
01227           assert(childlink->trie_prev);
01228           assert(!childlink->trie_next || child==((TrieLink_t<type> *RESTRICT)((size_t) childlink->trie_next + fieldoffset))->trie_prev);
01229           nodelink=childlink;
01230           state.count++;
01231         }
01232         nodelink=(TrieLink_t<type> *RESTRICT)((size_t) node + fieldoffset);
01233         state.count++;
01234         if(nodelink->trie_child[0])
01235         {
01236           state.lefts++;
01237           state.smallestkey=(size_t)-1;
01238           state.largestkey=0;
01239           triecheckvaliditybranch<trietype, type, fieldoffset, keyfunct>(head, nodelink->trie_child[0], bitidx-1, state);
01240           assert(state.smallestkey>=(size_t)1<<bitidx);
01241           assert(state.largestkey<(size_t)1<<(bitidx+1));
01242         }
01243         if(nodelink->trie_child[1])
01244         {
01245           state.rights++;
01246           state.smallestkey=(size_t)-1;
01247           state.largestkey=0;
01248           triecheckvaliditybranch<trietype, type, fieldoffset, keyfunct>(head, nodelink->trie_child[1], bitidx-1, state);
01249           assert(state.smallestkey>=(size_t)1<<bitidx);
01250           assert(state.largestkey<(size_t)1<<(bitidx+1));
01251         }
01252       }
01253     }
01254     assert(state.count==head->count);
01255     for(state.count=0, node=trieminmax<trietype, type, fieldoffset, keyfunct>(head, 0); node; (node=trienext<trietype, type, fieldoffset, keyfunct>(head, node)), state.count++)
01256 #if 0
01257       printf("%p\n", node)
01258 #endif
01259       ;
01260     if(state.count!=head->count)
01261     {
01262       assert(state.count==head->count);
01263     }
01264 #if 0
01265     printf("\n");
01266 #endif
01267     for(state.count=0, node=trieminmax<trietype, type, fieldoffset, keyfunct>(head, 1); node; (node=trieprev<trietype, type, fieldoffset, keyfunct>(head, node)), state.count++)
01268 #if 0
01269       printf("%p\n", node)
01270 #endif
01271       ;
01272     if(state.count!=head->count)
01273     {
01274       assert(state.count==head->count);
01275     }
01276 #if 0
01277     printf("\n");
01278 #endif
01279 #if !defined(NDEBUG) && 0
01280     if(count>50)
01281       printf("Of count %u, tops %.2lf%%, lefts %.2lf%%, rights %.2lf%%, leafs %.2lf%%\n", count, 100.0*tops/count, 100.0*lefts/count, 100.0*rights/count, 100.0*leafs/count);
